Former Bosasa COO, Angelo Agrizzi, is expected to face a grilling at the state capture inquiry on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - Former Bosasa COO, Angelo Agrizzi's cross-examination at the state capture inquiry has been postponed. Earlier this week, Commission Chairperson Justice Raymond Zondo announced that former Armscor CEO, Kevin Wakeford, would cross-examine Agrizzi and the company's former head of central business, Frans Vorster. READ: 'I'm not corrupt', Duduzane Zuma tells state capture inquiry The two implicated Wakeford, as a Bosasa beneficiary, of receiving monthly payments from the controversial company. Wakeford has denied the allegations.